<TITLE> Stocks shake off week's bearish trend </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 8 (bdnews24.com)The country's twin bourses shook off the week's bearish trend on the closing day, with over 60 percent of the traded issues going up. Dhaka Stock Exchange's benchmark closed 23 points higher, while the Chittagong Stock Exchange's key index gained 59 points. Market observers said the increased buying reflected the favourable prices provided by the week's poor performance. "The closing day usually sees some increased buying," said investment consultant Bashir Ahmed, of brokerage house Stock &.Bond. Heavyweights in banking continued to rise, while others remained more or less steady. Most of the insurers fell on profit taking following Wednesday's hike, with ICT shares following suit. Mutual funds rose after previous days' losses, while power and energy shares continued to climb. Dhaka stocks rose steeply from the opening bell and maintained their upward curve over the day, although the pace slowed. Turnover on the country's premier bourse remained steady at Tk 7.12 billion. The DSE general index or DGEN gained 23.15 points, or 0.78 percent, to close at 2982.68. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2493.91, up by 18.20 points, or 0.73 percent. The blue chip DSE-20 edged up 3.54 points, or 0.15 percent, to end on 2353.84. Of the scrips traded, 149 gained, 75 lost and six remained unchanged. Titas Gas came out as turnover leader with shares worth Tk 610.009 million traded, rising 8.26 percent to Tk 694. Banking sector bigwig AB Bank followed with a turnover of Tk 609.961 million, gaining 4.61 percent to end on 1053.50. Prime Finance had Tk 329.068 million in turnover, ending on Tk 1,652, edging up 0.56 percent. Beximco saw Tk 320.375 million worth of shares traded, slipping 0.10 percent to close at Tk 294. Grameen Mutual Fund One: Scheme 2 ended on Tk 57.20, up by 4.37 percent. Shares worth Tk 290.430 million changed hands. Among the other scrips on the turnover boardLanka Bangla Finance, Summit Power, Atlas Bangladesh Ltd and Aftab Automobilesall rose on buying pressure . Profit taking caused Beximco Pharmaceuticals to lose from the previous day. Chittagong Stocks Real estate, mutual funds and energy and engineering shares drove the indices up. The CSCX or selective categories index went up 58.36 points, or 0.88 percent, to close at 6679.71. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 10312.97, gaining 78.90 points, or 0.77 percent. The CSE-30 blue chip ended on 8075.80, up by 38.16 points, or 0.47 percent. Losers beat gainers by 66 to 34 and five scrips held steady. Turnover on the port city bourse fell to Tk 698.758 million from the previous day's total of Tk 909.179 million. AB Bank remained top of the turnover board, with shares of Tk 146.68 million changing hands. Grameen Mutual Fund One: Scheme 2, Beximco Ltd, Titas Gas and Eastern Housing Ltd were the other turnover leaders
